# Frontend UI Rule

## Scope
Applies to all files under `frontend/` for the Next.js App Router UI.

## Requirements
- Use TypeScript for all component and API-layer code; avoid `any`.
- Keep API contracts aligned with backend Pydantic schemas from [`backend/models/api_schemas.py`](mdc:backend/models/api_schemas.py) and boundary expectations in [`interfaces.mdc`](mdc:.cursor/rules/interfaces.mdc).
- Use `camelCase` field names in frontend request/response types.
- Keep API calls centralized in `frontend/lib/api.ts` rather than scattering raw `fetch` calls across components.
- Preserve clear loading/error/partial-success states in the workspace flow.
- For unimplemented backend endpoints, use explicit placeholder panels instead of fake hidden logic.

## UX Expectations
- The workspace should prioritize fast triage: ticket input, capsule output, and actionable status at a glance.
- Every required form field should be visibly marked and validated inline.
- Use accessible contrast and keyboard-friendly controls for all interactive UI elements.
- Keep component responsibilities narrow: presentational sections in `frontend/components/`, orchestration/state in `frontend/app/page.tsx`.
